================================================================================
ETHICAL USE ADDENDUM
================================================================================

In addition to the terms of the AGPL v3, use of this software is subject to
the following ethical constraints:

1. PROHIBITED USES
   This software SHALL NOT be used for:
   - Personal surveillance or tracking of individuals
   - Facial recognition or biometric identification
   - Individual consumer profiling or behavior prediction
   - Automated punishment or enforcement without human oversight
   - Sale or monetization of personal data
   - Any purpose that violates human dignity or privacy

2. REQUIRED PRACTICES
   Users of this software MUST:
   - Maintain human-in-the-loop for all consequential decisions
   - Operate with data minimization and aggregation at grid level
   - Implement and respect the ethical charter (ETHICAL_CHARTER.md)
   - Provide transparency about algorithmic decisions
   - Enable audit trails for accountability

3. DATA SOVEREIGNTY
   - Raw data must not be transferred across borders without explicit consent
   - Local data sovereignty must be respected
   - Federated learning approaches should be used for cross-border intelligence

4. ENFORCEMENT
   Violation of these ethical constraints constitutes a material breach of the
   license and terminates all rights granted under this license.

5. REPORTING
   Users must report any misuse or ethical violations to:
   ethics@urjarakshak.org

6. BINDING NATURE
   This ethical addendum is legally binding and integral to the license.
   It cannot be removed or modified without violating the license terms.

